children.subject:
for n players,
let 1 player divide the cake into n pieces and n-1 players gives n-1 preferences to parts of cake. now preferences of player who divided the cake is given to those parts where number of preferences to that part is not n-1 to make it n-1. now all parts of cake have n-1 preferences by n-1 players among n players. each part is recursively given to n-1 players who gave preference to that part. 
this mechanism ensures each players thinks he got at least 1/n part of cake but it requires cake to be cut into pieces which is in order of exponential power of n.
